The minister said Treasury's plan to grow the economy has been undermined by the recent downgrades, along with data showing a technical recession. JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba held a media briefing at Government Communication and Information System in Pretoria on Thursday.Among other things, he discussed economic growth and transformation in the country. He says all spheres, including government, business and labour have a role to play.He added that Treasury's plan to grow the economy has been undermined by the recent downgrades, along with data showing a technical recession.Moody's recently downgraded its rating by a notch, while S&amp;P Global and Fitch have theirs at BB+.The minister said President Jacob Zuma and other ministers discussed critical interventions at an emergency meeting on Wednesday night.WATCH: Gigaba's briefing below